717667f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 76th Street
717667f-a.text:
Broadway, east side, from 76th to 77th Streets, showing the Manhattan Congregational Church. About 1930 this church will be replaced by the 24-story Manhattan Towers Hotel, owned by and housing
the church.
December 21, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.

717668f-a.title: Manhattan: Broadway - 76th Street
717668f-a.text:
The Manhattan Congregational Church, 2162-2168 Broadway, east side, between 76th and 77th Streets. About 1930 this church will be replaced by the Manhattan Towers Hotel, owned by and housing the
church.
December 21, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
